Granarolo Investor May Help Fund Rival Parmalat Bid, Il Messaggero Says

-- B y   A r m o r e l   K e n n a
-- 
2011-04-15T06:26:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-15/granarolo-investor-may-help-fund-rival-parmalat-bid-il-messaggero-says.html
Granarolo SpA’s main investor, Gran
Latte, may contribute 500 million euros ($723 million) in a bid
for 60 percent of  Parmalat SpA (PLT) , daily Il Messaggero reported,
without saying where it got the information.  Italy’s state lender Cassa Depositi e Prestiti may invest
500 million euros, while  Intesa Sanpaolo SpA (ISP)  would fund about
120 million euros, according to the Italian newspaper.
 Mediobanca SpA (MB)  and BNP Paribas each are willing to invest as
much as 60 million euros each, Il Messaggero reported.  Lacteos Brasil SA is willing to contribute 200 million
euros, Il Messaggero reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Armorel Kenna in Milan at 
 akenna@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Celeste Perri at   cperri@bloomberg.net  